
Dispatcher Servlet
------------------------------------------------------------------65

    #   Acts as an entry point for handling all web applications
    #   Spring MCV follows 'Front Controller Pattern' with Dispatcher Servlet
    #   Check nice diagram here...#65
        
'HandlerMapping' & 'ViewResolver' Interface
------------------------------------------------------------------66

    #   HandlerMapping
        +   Is used to map an URL with Controller Class
        
    #   ViewResolver
        +   Used to resolve the view
            
        
Available HandlerMapping Implementations
------------------------------------------------------------------66

    #   ControllerClassNameHandlerMapping
    
        +   Returns a URL from the Controller Class
        +   Example (What it returns)
            -   DemoController  -> /demo
            
    #   BeanNameUrlHandlerMapping
                
        +   Is the default implementation used by Dispatcher Servlet
        +   Example
            -   /hello is dispatched to HelloController
            
    #   DefaultAnnotationHandlerMapping
        ...
        
Sub project that contains default Handler Implementations
------------------------------------------------------------------66
           
    #   Package
        +   org.springframework.web.servlet
        
    #   Sub project
        +   spring‚Äêwebmvc
                       
        
       